“MSS Man” watching you.

33
00:01:46,410 --> 00:01:49,940
MSS is China’s Ministry of State Security.

34
00:01:49,940 --> 00:01:53,060
They’re seriously scary dudes.

35
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:56,610
Or whatever zoomers call dudes these days.

36
00:01:56,610 --> 00:02:00,140
And China has very different laws about data
privacy.

37
00:02:00,140 --> 00:02:04,010
Namely, in China, there’s no privacy.

38
00:02:04,010 --> 00:02:07,209
Chinese law says Chinese companies that collect
user data

39
00:02:07,209 --> 00:02:11,530
have to share that data with the Chinese government
upon request.

40
00:02:11,530 --> 00:02:16,820
It’s not that Chinese authorities actively
monitor every user’s data in real time,

41
00:02:16,820 --> 00:02:21,440
but “The reality is that if and when Beijing
makes a demand,

42
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:25,540
it is hard for Chinese-based companies to
say no.”

43
00:02:25,540 --> 00:02:29,400
And that’s why it might be concerning that
a Chinese company—

44
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:31,750
ByteDance—owns TikTok,

45
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:36,180
