50
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:50,069
And it’s not just *me speculating* about
security risks.

51
00:02:50,069 --> 00:02:55,739
The US government has just opened a national
security investigation into TikTok.

52
00:02:55,739 --> 00:02:58,379
The investigation is led by CFIUS—

53
00:02:58,379 --> 00:03:01,730
the Committee on Foreign Investment in the
United States.

54
00:03:01,730 --> 00:03:05,380
CFIUS is an interdepartmental group of federal
government agencies.

55
00:03:05,380 --> 00:03:08,099
It investigates—and sometimes blocks—

56
00:03:08,099 --> 00:03:12,090
deals by foreign companies that might pose
a risk to US national security.

57
00:03:12,090 --> 00:03:17,879
For example, last year CFIUS blocked Chinese-owned
Ant Financial

58
00:03:17,879 --> 00:03:21,450
from buying financial services company MoneyGram.

59
00:03:21,450 --> 00:03:24,540
CFIUS also blocked IDG Energy Investment

60
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:28,300
from buying a bunch of oil and gas assets
in Texas.

61
00:03:28,300 --> 00:03:32,690
And now CFIUS is forcing a Chinese company
to sell Grindr,

62
00:03:32,690 --> 00:03:34,349
a gay dating app.

63
00:03:34,349 --> 00:03:38,390
Chinese gaming company Kunlun Tech had purchased
Grindr last year,

64
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:41,209
without going through a CFIUS review.

65
00:03:41,209 --> 00:03:44,900
